  "text": "To determine the platting efficiency on the substrate, the MM-4 cells (24 h after transduction) were plated in paired wells of 6-well plates («TPP») at a density of 200 cells per well in the complete growth medium (DMEM with 10 % NCS and 40 mg/ml gentamicin) and incubated at 37 o C in 5 % CO 2 . After 14 days the colonies of the cells were stained with the crystal violet dye («Sigma») [CITATION_1] . The number of colonies and their size were determined in each well using binocular magnifier BM-51-2 («LOMO», Russian Federation).",
